7/film/awards/labyrinth-wins-national-society-of-film-critics-award-1117956853/ |archive-date=July 13, 2018}}</ref><br><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.variety.com/profiles/people/Awards/31440/Meryl+Streep.html?dataSet=1 |title=Meryl Streep: Awards |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090907025157/http://www.variety.com/profiles/people/Awards/31440/Meryl%2BStreep.html?dataSet=1 |archive-date=7 September 2009 |access-date=23 January 2009}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2009 National Society of Film Critics Awards|2009]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[National Society of Film Critics Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n| ''[[Julie & Julia]]'' and ''[[Fantastic Mr. Fox (film)|Fantastic Mr. Fox]]''\n| {{draw|Runner-up}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hurt-locker-tops-critics-group-19058 |title='Hurt Locker' tops critics group nods |last=Kilday |first=Gregg |date=January 3, 2010 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=January 2, 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181215173532/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hurt-locker-tops-critics-group-19058 |archive-date=December 15, 2018}}</ref><br><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://articles.latimes.com/2010/jan/04/entertainment/la-et-national-critics4-2010jan04 |title='Hurt Locker' wins over National Film Critics |last=King |first=Susan |date=January 4, 2010 |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |access-date=January 2, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306121519/http://articles.latimes.com/2010/jan/04/entertainment/la-et-national-critics4-2010jan04 |archive-date=March 6, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2011 National Society of Film Critics Awards|2011]]\n| {{sort|Iron Lady|''[[The Iron Lady (film)|The Iron Lady]]''}}\n| {{draw|3rd place}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thewrap.com/awards/column-post/melancholia-named-best-picture-national-society-film-critics-